modules.description: Provides functions to allocate, map, and manipulate I/O memory pages, using page-aligned buffers. Works with Cstruct.t to handle raw memory without data duplication. Used for direct access to hardware memory regions in low-level system programming and virtualization environments.

Provides memory allocation and manipulation operations for page-aligned blocks, including allocation of multiple pages, conversion to and from Cstruct buffers, and address extraction. Works with bigarrays and Cstruct.t types, enabling low-level memory management. Used for efficient memory copying, debugging, and interfacing with system-level I/O operations.
